ccruncher.description:
Description: ------------------------------- 100 obligors 1 sector correl(S1,S1) = 0.20 2 ratings (dead and alive) transition values: P(alive->alive) = 0.9 P(alive->dead) = 0.1 P(dead->alive) = 0.0 P(dead->dead) = 1.0 12 months Each obligor has an asset with this profile: asset value at t=12 is 1 if obligor is alive and asset value at t=12 is 0 if obligor dead (default)
Expected Results: ------------------------------- This problem has an explicit solution. Can be solved using the simplified Merton approach (infinite obligors, exposure with same size, same default probability, gaussian process).
